There are two common approaches for teaching an introducto~ undergraduatecoursein artificial intelligence. The “depth-first” approachfocusesupon a few AI topics and covers them h detail. The “breadth-frst” approach coversmostof themajor topicsto presentanoverallpicture of AI and can also be used as a lead-in to an in-depth projector a more detailedcourse. This paper dkcusses the latter approach and presents a series of focus-issues, readiigs and assignments upon which a course like thk has been developed to meet the needs of a liberal arts audience.